   Here is the 79-16 roll call by which the
Senate voted to adopt a $268 billion defense spending bill for the
fiscal year that began Oct. 1.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to approve the
legislation and a ``no'' vote was a vote against final passage of
the bill.
   Voting ``yes'' were 42 Democrats and 37 Republicans.
   Voting ''no'' were 11 Democrats and five Republicans.
